posts.content:
@NickAbraham12 Inside our companies we’ve simplified this to: “how can I get everyone to stay past month 1” 

If you can just do that, you’re already 90% of the way there - it’s just…90% of the work to make that happen. 

But it’s a much clearer directive than “reduce churn”

posts.title:
@dklineii When someone asks for feedback, give them the real version.

Sugar-coating problems doesn't solve them.

People respect honesty more than they respect politeness.

